      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] harden Telegram transient recovery",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw can stay locally healthy while Telegram appears unresponsive when Telegram Bot API calls fail in two different transient ways:\n\n- Bot API HTTP 5xx responses from polling/setup paths crossed the isolated Telegram worker boundary as fatal server errors, causing ingress exits and supervisor backoff.\n- Slow or hanging provider sends could outlive the outbound message gateway client default timeout. The caller would abandon the request at 10s even though Telegram send handling is bounded at 60s, leaving ambiguous delivery state and no visible proof in the source chat.\n\nThe fix classifies Telegram Bot API HTTP 5xx responses as recoverable for polling/setup/control-plane contexts while keeping non-idempotent `send` context conservative. It also aligns the outbound message gateway default timeout with bounded provider sends, so callers receive the provider success/failure instead of an early local gateway timeout.\n\n## Summary\n\n- classify Telegram Bot API HTTP 5xx responses as recoverable for polling/setup/control-plane contexts\n- keep `send` context conservative to avoid duplicate visible messages\n- increase the outbound message gateway default timeout from 10s to 75s\n- document the `Bad Gateway` troubleshooting behavior for Telegram polling/startup instability\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Focused regression: `pnpm exec vitest run extensions/telegram/src/network-errors.test.ts` passes: 53 tests\n- Focused timeout contract: `pnpm exec vitest run src/infra/outbound/message-gateway-options.test.ts` passes: 3 tests\n- Local observed failure pattern: gateway health remained live, but Telegram logs repeated `Bad Gateway | Telegram ingress worker exited with code 1` after Bot API timeouts/502s\n- Local proof after applying the same classifier hotpatch earlier in the incident: safe gateway restart, Telegram account connected, and `openclaw message send --channel telegram ... --json` returned `ok: true` with a Telegram message id\n- Follow-up local proof for the timeout alignment: the installed hotpatch changed the visible failure from `GatewayTransportError: gateway timeout after 10000ms` to the provider-level `OutboundDeliveryError: Network request for sendMessage failed!` after the bounded provider timeout\n- Sanitized token-specific probe evidence: dummy/fake-token Telegram `getMe` probes returned immediately, while the configured real bot token established TLS and then timed out with zero bytes. This points to a Telegram-side/token-specific provider hang; the PR keeps OpenClaw behavior bounded and diagnosable rather than wedged or ambiguous.\n- Local `pnpm check:changed` from the earlier PR pass did not execute checks because the delegated Blacksmith Testbox `crabbox` binary failed its own sanity check before running",
